ions of derivatives and integrals to show how calculus is applied in these disciplines. Solutions to all exercises (even those involving proofs) are available to instructors upon request, making this book unique among texts in the field. Focuses on single variable calculus Provides a balance of precision and intuition Offers both routine and demanding exercises  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCalculusvTextbooks. 7aMATHEMATICS / Calculus.2bisacsh  aAccumulation point.  aAnalytic function.  aBisection, the method.  aCentral limit theorem, Conditional convergence.  aCountably infinite.  aDarboux sums.  aEscape velocity.  aExtrema.  aFluid resistance.  aGraph of a function.  aHeine-Borel lemma.  aInertial force.  aInfinite series.  aIntegrable.  aLindelof principle.  aLinear approximation.  aLogarithm.  aMean value theorem.  aMidpoint rule.  aObjective function.  aObserved fact.  aOsculating circle.  aPartial derivative.  aPartial fractions.  aPoisson flow.  aRatio test.  aReactor scram.  aScientific method.  aSecant lines.  aTangent lines.  aUniformly continuous.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044250240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691218229zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691218229423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691218229.jpg  a978-3-11-044250-2  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK